{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-14",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_14_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "La Paloma",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 734.8,
  "page_end_sec": 976.64,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.72,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 734.8,
      "end": 736.78,
      "text": "\"Looks like the gent's interested in a boat.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 737.04,
      "end": 737.74,
      "text": "\"Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 737.88,
      "end": 738.56,
      "text": "there's no law"
    },
    {
      "start": 738.68,
      "end": 739.18,
      "text": "against that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 739.28,
      "end": 740.04,
      "text": "or is there?"
    },
    {
      "start": 740.992,
      "end": 744.44,
      "text": "Luke said while Spade was folding the torn page and the crumpled"
    },
    {
      "start": 744.54,
      "end": 747.38,
      "text": "fragment together and putting them into his coat-pocket."
    },
    {
      "start": 748.18,
      "end": 749.04,
      "text": "\"You all through here now?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 749.38,
      "end": 749.48,
      "text": "\"Yes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 750.52,
      "end": 750.96,
      "text": "Thanks a lot,"
    },
    {
      "start": 751.0,
      "end": 751.2,
      "text": "Luke."
    },
    {
      "start": 752.1,
      "end": 754.0,
      "text": "Will you give me a ring as soon as he comes in?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 754.24,
      "end": 754.96,
      "text": "\"Sure.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 756.032,
      "end": 756.84,
      "text": "Spade went to the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 756.94,
      "end": 758.02,
      "text": "Business Office of the _Call_,"
    },
    {
      "start": 758.24,
      "end": 760.66,
      "text": "bought a copy of the previous day's issue,"
    },
    {
      "start": 760.87,
      "end": 762.22,
      "text": "opened it to the shipping-news-page,"
    },
    {
      "start": 762.3,
      "end": 763.96,
      "text": "and compared it with the"
    },
    {
      "start": 763.96,
      "end": 765.82,
      "text": "page taken from Cairo's wastebasket."
    },
    {
      "start": 765.96,
      "end": 767.76,
      "text": "The missing portion had read:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 768.16,
      "end": 772.18,
      "text": "5:17 A. M.—Tahiti from Sydney and Papeete."
    },
    {
      "start": 772.3,
      "end": 775.86,
      "text": "6:05 A. M.—Admiral Peoples from Astoria."
    },
    {
      "start": 776.56,
      "end": 777.9,
      "text": "8:07 A. M.—Caddopeak from San Pedro."
    },
    {
      "start": 780.62,
      "end": 784.46,
      "text": "8:17 A. M.—Silverado from San Pedro."
    },
    {
      "start": 785.16,
      "end": 787.66,
      "text": "8:05 A. M.—La Paloma from Hongkong."
    },
    {
      "start": 788.44,
      "end": 791.64,
      "text": "9:03 A. M.—Daisy Gray from Seattle."
    },
    {
      "start": 792.21,
      "end": 794.9,
      "text": "He read the list slowly and when he had finished",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 795.14,
      "end": 797.4,
      "text": "_Hongkong_ with a fingernail,"
    },
    {
      "start": 797.58,
      "end": 799.82,
      "text": "cut the list of arrivals from the paper with"
    },
    {
      "start": 799.82,
      "end": 802.2,
      "text": "his pocket-knife, put the rest of the paper and"
    },
    {
      "start": 802.3,
      "end": 805.16,
      "text": "Cairo's sheet into the wastebasket, and returned to"
    },
    {
      "start": 805.12,
      "end": 805.62,
      "text": "his office."
    },
    {
      "start": 806.14,
      "end": 808.6,
      "text": "He sat down at his desk, looked up a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 808.6,
      "end": 811.1,
      "text": "number in the telephone-book, and used the telephone."
    },
    {
      "start": 815.42,
      "end": 816.36,
      "text": "\"Kearny one four o one, please.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 816.9,
      "end": 818.48,
      "text": ". . . Where is the _Paloma_, in from"
    },
    {
      "start": 819.04,
      "end": 823.28,
      "text": "Hongkong yesterday morning, docked?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 823.58,
      "end": 825.24,
      "text": "He repeated the question. \"Thanks.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 825.38,
      "end": 825.94,
      "text": "He held the receiver-hook down with his thumb for a moment,"
    },
    {
      "start": 825.98,
      "end": 826.28,
      "text": "released it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 827.136,
      "end": 828.28,
      "text": "and said:"
    },
    {
      "start": 827.96,
      "end": 828.2,
      "text": "\"Davenport two o two o, please.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 829.7,
      "end": 831.02,
      "text": ". . . Detective bureau, please."
    },
    {
      "start": 831.52,
      "end": 832.32,
      "text": ". . . Is Sergeant Polhaus there?"
    },
    {
      "start": 833.76,
      "end": 834.24,
      "text": ". . . Thanks."
    },
    {
      "start": 834.88,
      "end": 836.84,
      "text": ". . . Hello, Tom, this is Sam Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 837.28,
      "end": 838.68,
      "text": ". . . Yes, I tried to"
    },
    {
      "start": 838.68,
      "end": 839.7,
      "text": "get you yesterday afternoon."
    },
    {
      "start": 840.58,
      "end": 842.82,
      "text": ". . . Sure, suppose you go to lunch with me."
    },
    {
      "start": 843.16,
      "end": 843.64,
      "text": ". . . Right.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 844.13,
      "end": 845.66,
      "text": "He kept the receiver to",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 845.66,
      "end": 847.62,
      "text": "his ear while his thumb worked the hook again."
    },
    {
      "start": 848.768,
      "end": 850.16,
      "text": "\"Davenport o one seven o, please.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 850.42,
      "end": 850.7,
      "text": ". . . Hello, this is Samuel"
    },
    {
      "start": 851.17,
      "end": 851.82,
      "text": "Hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 851.88,
      "end": 852.52,
      "text": "this is Samuel"
    },
    {
      "start": 852.9,
      "end": 853.02,
      "text": "Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 853.22,
      "end": 855.46,
      "text": "My secretary got a phone-message"
    },
    {
      "start": 855.46,
      "end": 856.5,
      "text": "yesterday that Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 856.6,
      "end": 857.88,
      "text": "Bryan wanted to see me."
    },
    {
      "start": 858.6,
      "end": 859.26,
      "text": "Will you ask him"
    },
    {
      "start": 859.26,
      "end": 861.06,
      "text": "what time's the most convenient for him?"
    },
    {
      "start": 861.32,
      "end": 862.14,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 862.34,
      "end": 863.28,
      "text": "Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 863.3,
      "end": 864.88,
      "text": "S-p-a-d-e.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 865.42,
      "end": 865.856,
      "text": "-D-E."
    },
    {
      "start": 866.34,
      "end": 867.82,
      "text": "A long pause."
    },
    {
      "start": 868.14,
      "end": 868.24,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 869.12,
      "end": 869.68,
      "text": "Two-thirty?"
    },
    {
      "start": 870.58,
      "end": 870.9,
      "text": "All right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 871.04,
      "end": 871.24,
      "text": "Thanks.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 872.3,
      "end": 873.68,
      "text": "He called a fifth number and said:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 873.9,
      "end": 874.44,
      "text": "\"Hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 874.5,
      "end": 874.84,
      "text": "darling."
    },
    {
      "start": 875.24,
      "end": 876.12,
      "text": "Let me talk to Sid?"
    },
    {
      "start": 876.34,
      "end": 877.32,
      "text": "Hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 877.38,
      "end": 877.64,
      "text": ". . . Hello, Sid—Sam."
    },
    {
      "start": 877.86,
      "end": 877.96,
      "text": "Sam."
    },
    {
      "start": 879.52,
      "end": 881.02,
      "text": "I've got a date with the District Attorney"
    },
    {
      "start": 881.02,
      "end": 882.58,
      "text": "at half-past two this afternoon."
    },
    {
      "start": 883.12,
      "end": 884.22,
      "text": "Will you give me a ring—"
    },
    {
      "start": 884.82,
      "end": 885.5,
      "text": "here or there—"
    },
    {
      "start": 885.58,
      "end": 886.16,
      "text": "around four,"
    },
    {
      "start": 886.53,
      "end": 888.3,
      "text": "just to see that I'm not in trouble?"
    },
    {
      "start": 889.2,
      "end": 890.8,
      "text": ". . . Hell with your Saturday afternoon golf:"
    },
    {
      "start": 891.2,
      "end": 892.7,
      "text": "your job's to keep me out of jail."
    },
    {
      "start": 893.56,
      "end": 893.68,
      "text": ". . . Right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 893.76,
      "end": 893.96,
      "text": "Sid."
    },
    {
      "start": 894.34,
      "end": 894.48,
      "text": "'Bye.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 895.1,
      "end": 896.72,
      "text": "He pushed the telephone away,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 897.02,
      "end": 897.66,
      "text": "yawned,"
    },
    {
      "start": 897.66,
      "end": 898.18,
      "text": "stretched,"
    },
    {
      "start": 898.76,
      "end": 899.72,
      "text": "felt his bruised temple,"
    },
    {
      "start": 900.2,
      "end": 900.94,
      "text": "looked at his watch,"
    },
    {
      "start": 901.06,
      "end": 902.64,
      "text": "and rolled and lighted a cigarette."
    },
    {
      "start": 903.52,
      "end": 905.9,
      "text": "He smoked sleepily until Effie Perine came in."
    },
    {
      "start": 907.08,
      "end": 908.16,
      "text": "Effie Perine came in smiling,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 908.44,
      "end": 909.72,
      "text": "bright-eyed and rosy-faced."
    },
    {
      "start": 910.4,
      "end": 911.46,
      "text": "\"Ted says it could be,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 911.58,
      "end": 912.08,
      "text": "she reported,"
    },
    {
      "start": 912.34,
      "end": 913.64,
      "text": "and he hopes it is."
    },
    {
      "start": 914.34,
      "end": 916.64,
      "text": "He says he's not a specialist in that field,"
    },
    {
      "start": 916.76,
      "end": 918.5,
      "text": "but the names and dates are all right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 918.82,
      "end": 920.52,
      "text": "and at least none of your authorities"
    },
    {
      "start": 920.52,
      "end": 922.88,
      "text": "or their works are out-and-out fakes."
    },
    {
      "start": 923.84,
      "end": 925.12,
      "text": "He's all excited over it.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 925.92,
      "end": 926.34,
      "text": "\"That's swell,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 926.62,
      "end": 928.85,
      "text": "as long as he doesn't get too enthusiastic"
    },
    {
      "start": 929.6,
      "end": 931.42,
      "text": "to see through it if it's phoney.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 932.1,
      "end": 932.42,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 932.46,
      "end": 933.18,
      "text": "he wouldn't—"
    },
    {
      "start": 933.18,
      "end": 933.72,
      "text": "not Ted!"
    },
    {
      "start": 934.56,
      "end": 936.3,
      "text": "He's too good at his stuff for that.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 937.28,
      "end": 937.78,
      "text": "\"Uh-huh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 938.58,
      "end": 940.34,
      "text": "the whole damned Perine family's wonderful,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 940.84,
      "end": 941.24,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 941.44,
      "end": 943.98,
      "text": "\"including you and the smudge of soot on your nose.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 945.02,
      "end": 945.8,
      "text": "\"He's not a Perine,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 945.94,
      "end": 946.68,
      "text": "he's a Christy.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 947.48,
      "end": 950.5,
      "text": "She bent her head to look at her nose in her vanity-case-mirror.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 951.36,
      "end": 952.3,
      "text": "\"I must've got that from"
    },
    {
      "start": 952.46,
      "end": 952.82,
      "text": "the fire.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 953.8,
      "end": 956.1,
      "text": "She scrubbed the smudge with the corner of a handkerchief.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 956.68,
      "end": 957.28,
      "text": "\"The Perine-Christy enthusiasm"
    },
    {
      "start": 958.62,
      "end": 959.56,
      "text": "ignite Berkeley?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 959.8,
      "end": 960.3,
      "text": "he asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 961.34,
      "end": 964.14,
      "text": "She made a face at him while patting her nose with a powdered pink",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 964.26,
      "end": 964.54,
      "text": "disc."
    },
    {
      "start": 965.18,
      "end": 966.92,
      "text": "\"There was a boat on fire when I came back."
    },
    {
      "start": 967.36,
      "end": 969.06,
      "text": "They were towing it out from the pier and the"
    },
    {
      "start": 969.16,
      "end": 970.9,
      "text": "smoke blew all over our ferry-boat.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 971.872,
      "end": 973.84,
      "text": "Spade put his hands on the arms of his chair.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 974.88,
      "end": 975.28,
      "text": "\"Were you near"
    },
    {
      "start": 975.36,
      "end": 976.64,
      "text": "enough to see the name of the boat?\""
    }
  ],
  "corrected": "claude"
}